HEADWORD: Insolate
<hw>In"so*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Insolated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Insolating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>insolatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>insolare</ets> to expose to the sun;
pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>sol</ets> the sun.]</ety> <def>To dry in,
